# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# ── Type ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#  feat:     New feature or sensor
#  fix:      Bug fix
#  refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#  docs:     Documentation only
#  test:     Adding or correcting tests
#  chore:    Build, CI, tooling, or dependency changes
#  style:    Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
#  perf:     Performance improvement
#
# ── Scope (optional) ─────────────────────────────────
#  coordinator, payback, tariff, sensor, config_flow,
#  diagnostics, api, energy, economics, analytics,
#  processing, ci, release, translations, docs
#
# ── Rules ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#  - Subject: imperative mood, lowercase, no period, ≤72 chars
#  - Body: wrap at 72 chars, explain *what* and *why*
#  - Footer: reference issues (Fixes #123) or note breaking changes
#  - Breaking changes: add BREAKING CHANGE: in footer
#
# ── Examples ──────────────────────────────────────────
#  feat(payback): add monthly first day of profit sensor
#  fix(coordinator): handle empty API response during backfill
#  refactor(sensor): split measurement sensors into own module
#  chore(release): bump version to 1.4.0
#  docs: update tariff preset notes in README
#  test(util): add parse_iso8601 edge case coverage
#
# ── Branch naming ─────────────────────────────────────
#  feature/<slug>   — new capability
#  fix/<slug>       — bug fix
#  refactor/<slug>  — structural improvement
#  chore/<slug>     — CI, deps, tooling
#  docs/<slug>      — documentation only
